Both are correct, just different encodings.
The `69` one is Code C with two digits per code point. The longer `68` one is Code B.

See also: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Code_128

If you want to force your code to also do the longer code B, you could set the [FORCE_CODE_SET](https://zxing.github.io/zxing/apidocs/com/google/zxing/EncodeHintType.html#FORCE_CODE_SET) encode hint to &quot;B&quot;.

